@node Scopo

@{B} Purpose @{UB}

AFoil permit to plot on screen and after on a printer
any aeronautics foil used in the RC model aircraft.

By a simple ASCII file that contain a table with
the point's coordinates, AFoil make a continuous AirFoil
image by a BSpline interpolation.

There are many sites with the dot's coordinates of many
kinds of AirFoil (NACA, E, ect...). That files are
tipically in ascii format and it's easy to convert them
to AFoil format.


@endnode



@node Requisiti

@{B} Requirements @{UB}


The elements needed for a correct function of AFoil are:

- An Amiga (of course!!!)
- Workbench 3.0
- Font CGTimes correctly installed (scalable font).
- A graphic printer and related driver.


@endnode



@node Funzioni

@{B} Features @{UB}


The Features that AFoil perform are:

- Full indipendence of display settings.
  (the workbench screen is cloned, also with graphics card)

- Screen preview with aspect ratio respected.

- Fully customizable AirFoil to plot, by an ascii file
  descriptor.

- Maximum number of dot for interpoling 50.

- Plotted AirFoil dimension from 40 mm to any
  dimension that allow your RAM, with a resolution of
  one millimeter.

- Printing on more A4 sheet for an airfoil with a dimension
  over 265mm.

- Automatic printer setting. You don't have to set
  the printer preference, AFoil do this for you.

- Printer density adjustable.

- Landscape or Portray printing.

- Fully localized in AmigaOS style.


@endnode



@node Installazione

@{B} Installation @{UB}


To install AFoil simply decompress the archive
with the options:

lha x AFoil.lha

directly in the destination drawer and copy the
catalog file in the relative language drawer.


If you don't have installed the CompuGraphics fonts,
then you should install the CGTimes from an AmigaOS
floppy or CD into your system.


@endnode



@node FormatoFile

@{B} File Format @{UB}


The descriptor file has six fields (lines):

1) Keyword: The first line MUST BE the keyword #spline#,
            this to recognize easly the file type by AFoil.

2) Name   : An ascii string rappresent the Name of AirFoil.
            This string will appear on screen and on printing dump.

3) SupAxisX: X coordinates of dot to interpolate that describe the top
             of AirFoil.

4) SupAxisY: Y coordinates of dot to interpolate that describe the top
             of AirFoil.

5) InfAxisX: X coordinates of dot to interpolate that describe the bottom
             of AirFoil.

6) InfAxisY: Y coordinates of dot to interpolate that describe the bottom
             of AirFoil.


The numbers precision is the same of float numbers.

A maximum of 10 digits (with the sign and the comma) are admitted for
the ASCII rappresentation of the float point numbers.

Is necessary to use a dot into the numbers rappresentation.

The number of points is automatically calculated by AFoil, but a limit of
50 dots exist.

There is only one limit between the X and Y dot's coordinates, for each
side (top and bottom) the number of X coordinates and the number of 
Y coordinates MUST BE the same.

Between the top and bottom X,Y coordinates there aren't limits.


@endnode



@node Compatibilita

@{B} Compatibility @{UB}


I've tested AFoil much time with my Amiga:

- AmigaOS 3.9, AmigaOS 3.1, AmigaOS 3.0
- A4000-40 25MHz
- 18MByte RAM
- 3.6 Gbyte HD0, 512 MByte HD1
- CyberVision 3D
- SCSI Oktagon, CDROM SCSI 4X, ZIP 100MByte, Scanner SCSI
- Epson printer with workbench driver


@endnode



@node Futuro

@{B} Future @{UB}


- Enlarge the printing dimension over the actual
  A4 limits of 265mm.

- Automatic printing of one AirFoil in many dimension
  on a single sheet.

@endnode



